        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> <b>Greetings, new here to the boards, so would like to first say hi and thanks for taking time to answer this question.   Been looking around here, lots and LOTS of good info to be had.</b></P><P>I have a lvl 29 Gnecro on E'ci who I really enjoy playing.<BR>(I created her due to getting the unholy crud scared out of my main when a spectre came running through camp following some poor soul, who turned out to be a high lvl necro (ahem Evilhempy) who is now my Necro's hero)</P><P>Anyway, up until another friend with a necro suggested that I camp the Millers in Qeynos hills, I had never used <b>Screaming Terror</b>.  I hit Mr. Miller with it and the missus instantly agro'd me; which I expected.  What I did not expect was for my <b>ST</b> to drop so fast, and have both of them  pounding on me and my pet.  I almost killed the Missus, when my pet was lost, and I was low on mana and life from fighting Mr. Miller.  Long story short, <b>they</b> camped me for about 15 min. after I FD'd, and then someone came and was talking to me, went to F9 and change view, hit 9 (attached to my sit/stand key) and you can guess what happend, Gnecro on a stick.</P><P><b>Is there a base time on ST?<BR>Does it last longer the more you use it?<BR>Does its length depend on lvl difference between you and mobs?</b></P><P>I really need to know.  Thanks for any useful input, and hope you got a good giggle out of my story.  I did, because I couldn't blame it on anyone but myself.</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Corto</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I can't give you exact figures but I can tell you what I've learned from experience.</P><P>ST seems to have a set duration of about 20 seconds or so.  It does not break early from what I've seen.  The problem is that it will not always make the MOB forget about you.  When I split a spawn with ST I usually cast ST on mob#1, cast dark and fear on mob#2 and then turn around and start watching the ST'd mob#1 to see what happens when ST wears off.  If ST wears off and he comes charging, I cast ST on him again and then turn around and cast a couple more spells on mob#2.</P><P>I have yet to try this but I hear it works...  If you cast ST on a MOB and then FD, he will forget about you when ST wears off.  So if this is true then you can ST mob#1, dark and fear mob#2 then FD.  Once ST wears off and mob#1 has forgotten about you you can stand up and continue killing mob#2.</P><P>I hope that makes sense.  Basically there is a set duration for ST but the memory wipe part of the spell does not always work.  As you get higher in level the memory wipe portion works less and less often.  I'm level 44 now and more than half of the mobs I ST do not forget about me.</P><P><BR>Insert witty comment and original artwork here.</P><P>Corto Muerte<BR>44 Gnecromancer</font></td>
